

                                Server Creation - Using Express


                1. create folder for Server

                2. create package.json -command: npm init

                3. Install express -command: npm i express

                4. create index.js file

                5. Import express to index.js

                6. Create app using express

                7. set port number for server

                8. To run server: command- node index.js/ nodemon index.js

                9. Resolve API - express-app.httpMethod(path,call back function)

                10. JWT token - To validate the user 

                    1. install jsonwebtoken - npm i jsonwebtoken

                    2. Import jsonwebtoken

                        10.1 Token Generation - sign({},secretkey)

                        10.2 Token Validate

                11. Middleware - 

                    11.1 Application specific

                    11.2 Router Specific

                12. Mongo DB - Connection

                    12.1 Install mongoose : npm i mongoose

                    12.2 create db.js

                    12.3 Import mongoose

                    12.4 state connection string

                    12.5 Create model

                    12.6 export model 

                13. Asynchronous event - Promise - 

                    13.1 Resolve State - then()

                    13.2 Reject state - catch 

                14. CORS - CROSS ORIGIN RESOURCE SHARING

                    14.1 install cors - npm i cors

                    14.2 Import cors in index.js